                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Glosses on ʻAbd Allāh ibn ʿUmar Bayḍāwī's Qurʿān commentary
                            entitled Anwār al-tanzīl on Sūrah Nūr (Sūrah 14) by Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad
                            Khafājī. The marginal notes in black are certainly by Khafājī himself,
                            and the manuscript itself may be an autograph of Khafājī (Mingana).
                            Written around 1640.</summary>

                        <msItem xml:id="manuscript_14301_item_1">
                            <locus from="" to=""/>
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="">Ḥāshiyat al-Khafājī ʿalā sharḥ
                                Sūrat al-Nūr li-l-Bayḍāwī</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt">حاشية الخفاجى على شرح سورة النور
                                للبيضاوى</title>
                            <author key="person_100625716">
                                <persName>Khafājī, Aḥmad ibn Muḥammad 1571 or 1572-1659</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ar">الخفاجي، احمد بن محمد</persName>
                            </author>
                            <note>
                                <p>Bayḍāwī's text is introduced by <quote>قوله</quote> in red.</p>
                                <p>Khafājī's name does not occur in the text itself but it is taken
                                    from the two following notes: a) three rhymed lines are added at
                                    the end on <locus from="74a">folio 74a</locus>, with the final
                                    note: <quote>نجز على يد مولفه احمد شهاب الدين ابن محمد المصرى
                                        غفر الله ذنوبه</quote>; b) an inscription in Turkish is
                                    written on <locus from="Flyleaf_ia">front flyleaf</locus> (after
                                    Khafājī's death) to the following effect: <quote>بو حاشيـهٔ
                                        شهابك اخرينده شهاب مر حومك خط لطيفلرى واردر</quote>. From
                                    these notes it is to be inferred that the manuscript is also an
                                    autograph of Khafājī.</p>
                                <p>The work is dedicated in the preface to the Shaikh ul-Islām
                                        <quote>يحيى بن زكرياء</quote></p>
                            </note>
                            <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
